WEBVTT

00:02.170 --> 00:03.537
Previously on "Chance"...

00:03.571 --> 00:04.705
D:
What I took off that shitbird

00:04.738 --> 00:05.806
back at
the massage parlor.

00:05.839 --> 00:07.108
Chance:
After you killed him.

00:07.141 --> 00:08.809
You call Blackstone
on that phone,

00:08.842 --> 00:11.112
it's a whole new day,
my brother. Buckle up.

00:11.145 --> 00:13.247
Blackstone: You told me he
put you on a bus. You were gone.

00:13.281 --> 00:14.482
Why the fuck
are you here?

00:14.515 --> 00:15.783
Nicole:
They drove me someplace

00:15.816 --> 00:17.118
and locked me
in this gross room.

00:17.151 --> 00:18.419
And I was so scared!

00:18.452 --> 00:20.421
Hey, Doc.
Detective Hynes.

00:20.454 --> 00:22.590
Detective Blackstone
beat his wife.

00:22.623 --> 00:24.125
He hit your daughter.

00:24.158 --> 00:25.959
Might be a part owner
in a brothel.

00:25.993 --> 00:27.061
He stalked and harassed you
and your friend,

00:27.095 --> 00:28.629
then he beat you up.

00:28.662 --> 00:29.963
The only thing I hate
more than a cop

00:29.997 --> 00:32.566
going after another cop is
a bad cop.

00:32.600 --> 00:33.667
Does that mean
you're gonna help me?

00:33.701 --> 00:35.269
I was looking
for Detective Hynes.

00:35.303 --> 00:36.670
When did you
last talk to him?

00:36.704 --> 00:38.472
A couple of days ago.
Why?

00:38.506 --> 00:40.841
He didn't come in for his shift
today. Didn't call either.

00:40.874 --> 00:42.443
Blackstone:
So, here's how it's gonna be.

00:42.476 --> 00:43.777
We are gonna meet and talk.

00:43.811 --> 00:45.513
Bring that second set of books
with you.

00:45.546 --> 00:48.482
You know the Ocean Park Motel?
Be there at 5:00 -- alone.

00:48.516 --> 00:50.784
I'll know if you're not. You
won't like what happens next.

00:50.818 --> 00:55.756
Chance:
Eldon Chance is a 55-year-old
right-handed neuropsychiatrist.

00:55.789 --> 00:57.591
Of late,
he is increasingly aware

00:57.625 --> 01:00.494
of a mental state he finds
to be dark and unstable.

01:00.528 --> 01:02.530
He fears he has been drawn
to the precipice

01:02.563 --> 01:04.832
of some new
and terrible reality,

01:04.865 --> 01:06.334
and that now, having stumbled,

01:06.367 --> 01:08.869
he will be unable
to keep from falling.

01:11.139 --> 01:14.142
**

01:57.050 --> 01:58.919
[ Waves crashing ]

02:05.793 --> 02:08.796
**

02:12.366 --> 02:17.671
Man: On the other side!

02:17.705 --> 02:19.573
There!

02:19.607 --> 02:21.475
[ Police radio chatter ]
Come over here!

02:27.615 --> 02:31.385
Breathing!
Yeah.

02:31.419 --> 02:32.720
[ Doors shut ]

02:32.753 --> 02:34.888
[ Engine starts
and radio chatter ]

02:34.922 --> 02:36.590
[ Siren wails ]

02:36.624 --> 02:38.726
[ Heart monitor
beeping steadily ]

02:43.431 --> 02:45.199
Where am I?

02:45.233 --> 02:47.067
What is this?

02:47.100 --> 02:49.570
You're in an ambulance,
Dr. Chance,

02:49.603 --> 02:51.705
on the way
to the hospital.

02:51.739 --> 02:54.908
You had a real bad fall.
You're a lucky man.

03:11.825 --> 03:14.495
Oh, my God.

03:14.528 --> 03:17.598
Jaclyn.

03:17.631 --> 03:20.601
Are you okay?

03:20.634 --> 03:23.304
What happened?

03:23.337 --> 03:25.306
Tell me what happened.

03:30.043 --> 03:33.113
Oh.

03:33.146 --> 03:36.116
Please.
Please talk to me.

03:36.149 --> 03:38.185
Please talk to me.

03:38.218 --> 03:40.788
I tried.

03:40.821 --> 03:44.358
But you know that,
I fucking tried.

03:44.392 --> 03:48.762
Tried what, to fly?
My God, Eldon, you're a local.

03:48.796 --> 03:50.531
You know those cliffs.

03:50.564 --> 03:52.199
What were you doing out there
at night?

03:52.232 --> 03:53.934
You have a death wish?

03:53.967 --> 03:56.270
I -- I just can't
remember.

03:56.304 --> 03:57.805
I -- I don't know --

03:57.838 --> 03:59.540
Don't worry about that
right now.

03:59.573 --> 04:01.809
You need your rest.

04:01.842 --> 04:03.811
Did you see her?

04:03.844 --> 04:06.647
Would that be Jaclyn?
Yeah. Is she --

04:06.680 --> 04:10.284
There's no one here, hon.
I just heard you say that name.

04:10.318 --> 04:13.954
[ Sighs ]

04:13.987 --> 04:15.689
Hey, I need my phone.

04:15.723 --> 04:19.627
No. No phone right now.
You need to rest.

04:19.660 --> 04:23.096
Listen, either
you're going to remember...

04:24.998 --> 04:26.934
...or you're not.

04:28.936 --> 04:31.305
Nicole: Dad?

04:31.339 --> 04:32.706
Dad?

04:32.740 --> 04:37.244
[ Heart monitor
beeping steadily ]

04:37.277 --> 04:39.212
Hi.

04:39.246 --> 04:40.981
They said you have a concussion
and broken bones,

04:41.014 --> 04:43.984
but you're gonna be okay.

04:44.017 --> 04:47.555
Are you?
Doesn't look like you are.

04:47.588 --> 04:49.022
Where's your mother?

04:49.056 --> 04:51.625
She went to get
more coffee.

04:54.762 --> 04:57.164
So what happened?

04:57.197 --> 05:01.335
I mean,
what really happened?

05:01.369 --> 05:04.204
I'm...
I don't remember.

05:04.237 --> 05:06.874
Well, what about
your scary friend?

05:06.907 --> 05:09.877
Did he do anything?

05:09.910 --> 05:12.580
I don't know.

05:12.613 --> 05:15.282
Probably
best to keep him

05:15.315 --> 05:20.954
between the two of us
for now, okay?

05:20.988 --> 05:26.226
I'll say I'm not so good
right now.

05:26.259 --> 05:30.063
But neither are you.
Are you?

05:34.267 --> 05:36.303
[ Monitor beeps quickly, stops ]

05:39.407 --> 05:42.876
But we're gonna fix
what's wrong with us.

05:42.910 --> 05:46.113
The both of us.

05:46.146 --> 05:49.149
That's what matters.

05:49.182 --> 05:53.621
Well, you say stuff like that,
and then you just leave.

05:53.654 --> 05:57.224
And then you fall off
a stupid cliff.

05:57.257 --> 05:59.993
Yeah, it's
a really stupid cliff.

06:00.027 --> 06:01.495
[ Chuckles ]

06:08.035 --> 06:10.538
[ Rattling ]

06:24.217 --> 06:25.986
[ Gasping ]

06:43.871 --> 06:46.339
The fuck
were you thinking, Doc?

06:48.676 --> 06:50.644
[ Gasping ]

06:50.678 --> 06:53.180
[ Siren wails distantly ]

06:57.918 --> 07:01.689
Dr. Chance, hey.

07:01.722 --> 07:04.658
Detective Newsome, SFPD.

07:04.692 --> 07:07.461
Sorry if I startled you.

07:07.495 --> 07:11.164
No, it's okay.
I -- I...

07:11.198 --> 07:13.033
I was dreaming, I guess.

07:13.066 --> 07:16.203
Anyone show you
a newspaper?

07:16.236 --> 07:18.371
You're in there.

07:18.405 --> 07:23.143
Although just "San Francisco
Bay's doctor, name withheld."

07:23.176 --> 07:24.912
Fell of a cliff.

07:24.945 --> 07:26.714
Almost famous.

07:26.747 --> 07:30.083
I'm guessing it was the car
accident that distracted you.

07:30.117 --> 07:31.919
What do you think?

07:38.692 --> 07:40.360
Thank you.

07:40.393 --> 07:42.863
I -- I don't remember
a car accident.

07:42.896 --> 07:45.499
Old man in an old car,
T-boned a new Mercedes.

07:45.533 --> 07:47.835
Pretty much
right on top of you.

07:47.868 --> 07:49.570
Wall hadn't been
under repair,

07:49.603 --> 07:51.539
it probably
wouldn't have fallen.

07:51.572 --> 07:54.441
You really --
You don't remember?

07:54.474 --> 07:57.511
With an injury
such as mine...

07:57.545 --> 08:01.582
your retrograde component
can be buried.

08:01.615 --> 08:06.787
Some people
can lose months, years.

08:06.820 --> 08:09.022
Over time, some people can
remember everything.

08:09.056 --> 08:10.758
Others never do.

08:10.791 --> 08:12.893
Oh.

08:12.926 --> 08:15.696
You mind me asking...

08:15.729 --> 08:19.266
why you care
what I remember?

08:19.299 --> 08:21.401
This about the accident?

08:21.434 --> 08:24.304
A lot of things
went down that night.

08:24.337 --> 08:26.640
The Mercedes the old man hit
fled the scene.

08:26.674 --> 08:28.576
Found the car
abandoned later.

08:28.609 --> 08:30.243
Passenger's
still at large.

08:30.277 --> 08:32.145
That's terrible.

08:32.179 --> 08:33.714
Yeah.

08:33.747 --> 08:38.218
But that's
just one piece of it.

08:38.251 --> 08:41.054
There was a homicide in progress
almost at the same time.

08:41.088 --> 08:44.592
Multiple victims at a motel
not too far away.

08:44.625 --> 08:47.227
My God.

08:47.260 --> 08:48.729
Yeah.

08:48.762 --> 08:50.230
And an Oakland cop was involved,
so, of course,

08:50.263 --> 08:51.765
the media's been
going crazy.

08:51.799 --> 08:54.902
Do you remember
why you were out there?

08:54.935 --> 08:57.738
I was, uh...

08:57.771 --> 08:59.006
I was just walking.

08:59.039 --> 09:02.109
You know,
I wanted to clear my head.

09:02.142 --> 09:04.344
Been having a lot of trouble
with our daughter, and --

09:04.377 --> 09:06.179
Sure.
I get that.

09:06.213 --> 09:09.783
Name Raymond Blackstone
mean anything?

09:09.817 --> 09:12.753
To me?
No, I -- I don't think so.

09:12.786 --> 09:15.088
No.

09:15.122 --> 09:16.624
Why, is he --

09:16.657 --> 09:18.125
The cop
I just mentioned.

09:18.158 --> 09:21.094
He was the victim --
one of the victims.

09:21.128 --> 09:24.798
A witness placed him
near the Cliff House earlier.

09:24.832 --> 09:27.534
You recall seeing anyone nearby
before you fell?

09:27.567 --> 09:30.103
No, I haven't --

09:30.137 --> 09:34.608
I don't remember.

09:34.642 --> 09:37.177
You said...

09:37.210 --> 09:40.047
You said multiple victims?

09:40.080 --> 09:44.351
Yeah.
It's a real shit show.

09:44.384 --> 09:48.321
Uh, I'm gonna take your clothes,
if that's okay.

09:48.355 --> 09:49.790
What?

09:49.823 --> 09:51.224
I want to look them over,
to see if maybe

09:51.258 --> 09:53.994
you and Blackstone
came into contact or...

09:54.027 --> 09:56.830
maybe were victims
of the same perp, even.

09:56.864 --> 09:59.132
Grasping at straws maybe,
or maybe not.

09:59.166 --> 10:00.968
Maybe you'll remember.

10:01.001 --> 10:04.738
Or maybe we'll figure it all out
without you.

10:04.772 --> 10:07.775
**

10:11.211 --> 10:12.245
[ Sighs ]

10:20.921 --> 10:22.522
[ Woman speaking over PA ]

10:22.555 --> 10:24.324
You okay there, Eldon?

10:24.357 --> 10:27.160
[ Sighs ]

10:27.194 --> 10:32.532
You know, Ginley, I have
questioned a million patients...

10:32.565 --> 10:35.703
without ever really knowing
what it's like to have

10:35.736 --> 10:37.838
a period of time
in which something

10:37.871 --> 10:42.075
life-changing happened
that can't be accounted for.

10:42.109 --> 10:45.345
Like there's something terrible
to one's sense of the world.

10:45.378 --> 10:48.548
I'm sure it does.

10:48.581 --> 10:52.219
All those disorders,
all those pathologies --

10:52.252 --> 10:55.188
I can imagine that
that is the thing I've become.

10:55.222 --> 10:57.124
Some sort of
walking repositories

10:57.157 --> 10:59.392
of all the mental illness
I've ever dealt with.

10:59.426 --> 11:02.229
If that's what you're imagining,
cut it out.

11:02.262 --> 11:03.731
I brought you something.

11:06.066 --> 11:10.470
When the police asked for your
clothes, I tucked this away.

11:10.503 --> 11:13.640
EMTs said you had it on you
when you fell.

11:13.673 --> 11:15.876
Thought it might be something
you'd like to keep track of.

11:15.909 --> 11:18.578
[ Sighs ]

11:18.611 --> 11:20.480
And, uh, also this.

11:20.513 --> 11:23.416
I turned it off
to save the battery.

11:23.450 --> 11:29.456
And...
whatever this is.

11:29.489 --> 11:32.459
I don't know
what the hell's going on.

11:32.492 --> 11:35.829
I've just...always thought
of you as one of the good ones.

11:35.863 --> 11:38.331
One of the few.

11:38.365 --> 11:40.600
So...

11:40.633 --> 11:43.336
Am I gonna be sorry?

11:43.370 --> 11:45.305
I hope not.

11:45.338 --> 11:46.840
Me, too.

12:07.660 --> 12:11.164
[ Line ringing ]

12:11.198 --> 12:14.501
Woman: You have reached a number
that has been disconnected.

12:20.007 --> 12:22.542
[ Line ringing ]

12:23.676 --> 12:25.378
Carl: You've reached
Allan's Antiques.

12:25.412 --> 12:27.214
No one here is available
to take your ca--

12:27.247 --> 12:29.216
Your family's here
for you.

12:32.319 --> 12:34.487
Like you don't know
hospital policy.

12:36.089 --> 12:37.825
Get in the chair.

12:40.593 --> 12:42.395
[ Sighs ]

12:47.167 --> 12:50.737
Yeah, a town car is fine.

12:50.770 --> 12:54.474
6600 Post Street.

12:54.507 --> 12:57.144
How long?

12:57.177 --> 12:58.545
That's great.

12:58.578 --> 13:01.481
Uh, just tell the driver
I'll be out front.

13:01.514 --> 13:03.716
[ Knock on door ]

13:12.425 --> 13:14.862
I got to the hospital,
they said you'd been discharged.

13:14.895 --> 13:18.065
Yeah, yeah.

13:18.098 --> 13:20.934
This morning.

13:20.968 --> 13:23.570
You just missed Christina
and Nicole.

13:23.603 --> 13:24.905
Hmm.

13:28.241 --> 13:31.078
What the hell, Eldon?

13:31.111 --> 13:34.581
I, uh --
I was out for a walk.

13:34.614 --> 13:36.917
It's on every newscast.

13:36.950 --> 13:39.352
I guess we weren't the only ones
who didn't like him.

13:39.386 --> 13:41.955
But still.

13:41.989 --> 13:46.793
Uh, it's a dangerous game --
even for the good cops.

13:46.826 --> 13:48.461
But you were out there.

13:48.495 --> 13:51.431
You were right there,
for Christ's sake.

13:51.464 --> 13:53.733
Have you said anything?
To whom?

13:53.766 --> 13:56.269
They're asking for people
to come forward.

13:56.303 --> 14:01.708
They are asking for people with
information to come forward.

14:01.741 --> 14:04.711
Anyway,
they have already showed up.

14:04.744 --> 14:06.246
And?

14:06.279 --> 14:09.082
And nothing.

14:09.116 --> 14:12.519
I went for a walk, Suzanne,
and I fell.

14:14.621 --> 14:18.125
What about her?

14:18.158 --> 14:21.461
I don't know.
I haven't heard from her.

14:21.494 --> 14:23.296
They haven't released the names
of the other victims.

14:23.330 --> 14:25.465
She could have been there.
She could be dead.

14:25.498 --> 14:28.168
[ Sighs ]

14:28.201 --> 14:30.337
I mean, what's the point
of lying to you?

14:30.370 --> 14:34.174
I -- I can't...
get it out of my mind,

14:34.207 --> 14:36.676
finding her, finding out
what happened to her.

14:36.709 --> 14:38.011
I don't even know
how I'd start.

14:38.045 --> 14:41.248
How you would explain it
to the police.

14:41.281 --> 14:43.316
The police, who are probably
looking for her themselves,

14:43.350 --> 14:45.118
if she's not dead.

14:45.152 --> 14:47.620
You know, since her husband just
got murdered out by the beach.

14:47.654 --> 14:49.322
And the fact
that you knew her

14:49.356 --> 14:54.094
probably isn't information
you gave them, is it?

14:54.127 --> 14:57.264
I came here
to see how you were.

14:57.297 --> 15:01.101
And now I have.

15:01.134 --> 15:03.236
And you're alive.

15:07.340 --> 15:11.144
If you ever get better,
you let me know.

15:32.199 --> 15:34.701
It's all right.
I wasn't followed.

15:34.734 --> 15:39.406
Ah! Like Lazarus
raised from the dead.

15:39.439 --> 15:42.809
Sorry not to have braved
the confines of the hospital.

15:42.842 --> 15:45.545
Seemed the wisest decision,
considering.

15:46.546 --> 15:50.183
You have to tell me what
happened back there...now.

15:50.217 --> 15:52.185
What do you remember,
Doc?

15:54.621 --> 15:57.024
I remember Blackstone
in front of me.

15:57.057 --> 15:59.192
I remember the Mercedes
behind me.

15:59.226 --> 16:01.728
And then...nothing.

16:01.761 --> 16:04.697
No shit.
That's pretty crazy.

16:04.731 --> 16:08.201
People are dead.
He's dead.

16:08.235 --> 16:10.837
Is she?
Did I kill him?

16:10.870 --> 16:12.539
You're the only ones
I can talk to about this.

16:12.572 --> 16:14.341
You got to tell me
what you know now!

16:14.374 --> 16:16.776
You'll get all of it, but
right now, you need to relax.

16:16.809 --> 16:19.646
I mean, it wasn't long ago,
you fell of a fucking cliff.

16:22.315 --> 16:25.918
For starters,
Boss saved your ass.

16:25.952 --> 16:29.522
It was you?
The old man in the accident?

16:29.556 --> 16:31.258
Who said old?

16:31.291 --> 16:33.693
That's your word,
not mine.

16:33.726 --> 16:37.030
But, yes,
I did my little part.

16:37.064 --> 16:40.467
We parked and waited
until we saw them come out.

16:40.500 --> 16:43.503
**

16:50.910 --> 16:53.113
Blackstone
and two thugs --

16:53.146 --> 16:56.015
We trailed them from the motel
to the beach.

17:04.824 --> 17:08.061
D: Pull over.

17:08.095 --> 17:09.462
All right.

17:09.496 --> 17:11.164
You park
further down, okay?

17:11.198 --> 17:12.599
Somewhere by
the Great Highway

17:12.632 --> 17:15.102
where you can get eyes
on the doc and the cop.

17:15.135 --> 17:17.170
I'm gonna stick with the guys
in the Mercedes.

17:17.204 --> 17:19.005
If Doc Chance gets to
where he's supposed to be,

17:19.038 --> 17:21.841
they're gonna try rolling up on
his six -- That's what I'd do.

17:21.874 --> 17:24.111
That's you and the doc
against those three.

17:24.144 --> 17:25.945
They're
armed and dangerous.

17:25.978 --> 17:28.481
Keep your cell open,
radio contact.

17:37.824 --> 17:43.196
It was about
to be perfect, Doc...

17:43.230 --> 17:45.832
at which point, you went full-on
headless chicken.

17:45.865 --> 17:50.537
[ Cellphone buzzing ]

17:50.570 --> 17:53.440
What the fuck, Doc?

17:53.473 --> 17:55.108
You started telling me
we had to abort,

17:55.142 --> 17:56.843
said you were
going to Land's End,

17:56.876 --> 17:59.112
but then you don't even do that.
You went down those stairs.

17:59.146 --> 18:01.781
Chance: Yeah, that's when I saw
those guys in the Mercedes.

18:01.814 --> 18:04.151
That's why
I was there to begin with.

18:04.184 --> 18:06.018
I-I thought about trying
to head you off at the pass,

18:06.052 --> 18:07.654
but then you never showed.

18:07.687 --> 18:08.888
You weren't answering
your fucking phone, either.

18:08.921 --> 18:11.358
I was scared, D.
No shit.

18:11.391 --> 18:14.794
I look, there you are,
middle of the fucking sidewalk,

18:14.827 --> 18:18.198
under the lights, in plain sight
going back the way you came.

18:18.231 --> 18:20.233
A blind man could see
where that was headed.

18:20.267 --> 18:23.370
We need an air strike,
brother -- right fucking now.

18:23.403 --> 18:25.104
[ Phone beeps ]

18:32.345 --> 18:35.482
Thing you got to love
about Carl --

18:35.515 --> 18:38.251
You ask him to crash his car,
he just does it --

18:38.285 --> 18:40.920
no questions,
no hesitation.

18:40.953 --> 18:43.256
Let's face it --
The guy's got balls.

18:56.636 --> 18:59.272
Carl: I lost track of everything
in the collision.

18:59.306 --> 19:01.574
Hadn't seen you or him.

19:01.608 --> 19:03.943
But seeing the place
where the wall was broken,

19:03.976 --> 19:05.712
I just had a feeling.

19:05.745 --> 19:07.514
The crash
got everybody's attention,

19:07.547 --> 19:09.115
let me
get out in the open.

19:09.148 --> 19:11.218
That's when I saw
Blackstone's car go.

19:11.251 --> 19:13.286
You weren't
in my line of sight, Doc.

19:13.320 --> 19:15.121
It was dark,
but I saw him leaving.

19:15.154 --> 19:17.357
I figured he'd killed you
or grabbed you.

19:17.390 --> 19:19.392
Either way,
I knew where he was going.

19:19.426 --> 19:21.928
Everything you told me
about him and her,

19:21.961 --> 19:24.297
I knew
he wasn't leaving alone.

19:50.089 --> 19:52.725
Blade carries cloth
into the wound,

19:52.759 --> 19:54.060
helps staunch the flow.

19:54.093 --> 19:55.662
[ Shuddering breathing ]

19:55.695 --> 19:57.830
Along with that,
you hold the blade in place

19:57.864 --> 20:00.166
for a two-count,
there won't be enough pressure

20:00.199 --> 20:02.435
left in the system
to drive the blood.

20:02.469 --> 20:04.471
[ Gasps ]

20:04.504 --> 20:06.506
[ Exhales deeply ]

20:06.539 --> 20:08.408
What are you saying?

20:08.441 --> 20:10.743
Congratulations.

20:10.777 --> 20:14.080
But if the --
if the aortic arch was pierced,

20:14.113 --> 20:16.283
there wasn't enough pressure
left in his system --

20:16.316 --> 20:17.750
I didn't say
you were perfect.

20:17.784 --> 20:18.985
You missed
the aortic arch.

20:19.018 --> 20:20.987
Knife went
into his heart.

20:21.020 --> 20:22.522
That's why I could see
the blade moving

20:22.555 --> 20:24.491
every time his heart
tried to pump.

20:24.524 --> 20:26.293
Cardiac tamponade.
Yeah.

20:26.326 --> 20:28.328
Heart knots up
around the blade.

20:28.361 --> 20:31.097
Pericardium
fills with blood.

20:31.130 --> 20:33.333
The exact placement of the blade
and severity of the wound

20:33.366 --> 20:35.435
will determine
exactly how long it takes

20:35.468 --> 20:37.604
for the pericardium
to completely fill,

20:37.637 --> 20:39.138
choke off the heart.

20:39.171 --> 20:41.374
But until then,
it's still treatable.

20:41.408 --> 20:43.776
Pretty much fatal
pretty much all the time, Doc,

20:43.810 --> 20:45.778
treated or not.

20:45.812 --> 20:48.281
Wha -- uh...
You were there.

20:48.315 --> 20:49.849
You could have
called someone

20:49.882 --> 20:52.485
instead of pulling the blade
and accelerating the bleed.

20:52.519 --> 20:54.454
Called who, said what?

20:54.487 --> 20:56.989
It was his choice, Doc --
Blackstone's.

20:57.023 --> 20:59.459
He knew it, he made it.

20:59.492 --> 21:01.394
He could have gone
and tried to get himself help.

21:01.428 --> 21:03.996
But he went
back to her instead.

21:06.666 --> 21:09.402
[ Keys jingle ]

21:09.436 --> 21:11.338
Well, where is she?

21:11.371 --> 21:14.273
I don't know where she is.
She's gone.

21:16.343 --> 21:18.411
When you say gone...

21:18.445 --> 21:20.547
I say I don't know.

21:20.580 --> 21:23.716
He was dead, I unlocked
her cuffs, and that's it.

21:23.750 --> 21:25.418
She could be
anywhere now.

21:25.452 --> 21:29.088
The important thing is the lady
you wanted free is free,

21:29.121 --> 21:30.723
Doc, and you did it.

21:30.757 --> 21:33.092
You did all of it.
How does it feel?

21:33.125 --> 21:34.661
Yeah, but I didn't.
I didn't.

21:34.694 --> 21:37.930
It wasn't me, it was you
pulling out the blade.

21:37.964 --> 21:39.899
That you put in.

21:39.932 --> 21:41.768
She's free,
and you killed him.

21:41.801 --> 21:44.170
How does it feel?

21:44.203 --> 21:46.205
[ Sighs ]

21:46.238 --> 21:49.576
I don't know.

21:49.609 --> 21:52.445
How would you feel, D...

21:52.479 --> 21:53.946
if someone told you
you'd done something like that,

21:53.980 --> 21:56.683
you can't remember it?

21:56.716 --> 21:57.617
It's like...

21:57.650 --> 21:58.951
[ Sighs ]

21:58.985 --> 22:01.588
It's like being lost
in my own home.

22:01.621 --> 22:04.757
It's terrifying.

22:04.791 --> 22:06.092
[ Sighs ]

22:06.125 --> 22:08.761
So, what happens now?

22:15.402 --> 22:17.837
Try not
to be a stranger.

22:24.243 --> 22:26.413
See you, Doc.

22:47.266 --> 22:50.903
**

22:50.937 --> 22:52.605
Dr. Marks:
So, general concerns.

22:52.639 --> 22:54.507
The nature and type
of friendships she has,

22:54.541 --> 22:57.309
her choice in role models,
love interests.

22:57.343 --> 22:59.912
Only one in that department,
but yeah.

22:59.946 --> 23:02.782
And her affiliated behavior,

23:02.815 --> 23:06.085
her willingness to engage
in risk-taking behavior.

23:06.118 --> 23:08.187
Not unheard of
among teenagers.

23:08.220 --> 23:10.189
[ Chuckles softly ]
No, of course.

23:10.222 --> 23:12.459
Frontal lobe development is
a beautiful thing --

23:12.492 --> 23:14.694
when and if.

23:14.727 --> 23:18.130
Uh, the Yale-Brown
Obsessional Scale is something

23:18.164 --> 23:19.832
I've used
in my own practice.

23:19.866 --> 23:22.969
If I am not mistaken, there's
an adolescent version, as well.

23:23.002 --> 23:24.704
Yes, there is.

23:24.737 --> 23:28.274
And we can
look into that.

23:28.307 --> 23:31.878
I will also say that...

23:31.911 --> 23:35.114
she's never been one
to take things lightly.

23:35.147 --> 23:38.050
You know, she gets interested
in something, she's...

23:38.084 --> 23:41.888
a heat-seeking missile --
all-in.

23:41.921 --> 23:44.791
It's the upside to obsession,
I suppose.

23:44.824 --> 23:46.659
It's not all
doom and gloom.

23:46.693 --> 23:49.361
And there is also
a potential for illumination,

23:49.395 --> 23:51.197
but that balance
has to be found.

23:51.230 --> 23:52.965
And that's what you think
she may be losing --

23:52.999 --> 23:55.702
the balance.

23:55.735 --> 23:59.639
I, myself, am...

23:59.672 --> 24:03.743
I am not without
certain obsessive proclivities.

24:03.776 --> 24:07.346
You think there may be
a genetic component in Nicole.

24:07.379 --> 24:09.248
Yeah, I do.

24:14.286 --> 24:16.923
Dr. Marks is ready
for you.

24:16.956 --> 24:19.325
You were
in there forever.

24:19.358 --> 24:20.560
If you already
told her everything,

24:20.593 --> 24:21.994
then why do I have to
go in there?

24:22.028 --> 24:24.330
You'll like her.
Go on.

24:24.363 --> 24:26.065
I'll be here
when you get out.

24:30.069 --> 24:31.403
Hey.

24:38.545 --> 24:41.548
**

24:45.618 --> 24:48.454
Oh, hey!
There you are!

24:54.627 --> 24:56.495
[ Horn honks ]

25:00.066 --> 25:02.034
Hey, Doc.

25:02.068 --> 25:04.771
That's a cute cup of coffee
you got there.

25:04.804 --> 25:08.274
My God, Detective Hynes.
You're all right.

25:08.307 --> 25:11.243
I thought Blackstone might have
gotten to you somehow.

25:11.277 --> 25:13.145
Yeah, well...

25:13.179 --> 25:15.081
he would have.

25:15.114 --> 25:17.316
He tried.

25:17.349 --> 25:19.051
You know,
I started to look into him

25:19.085 --> 25:20.987
right after
I saw you last.

25:21.020 --> 25:22.755
Spoke to a guy
in Oakland Vice

25:22.789 --> 25:25.124
who I thought
was good people.

25:25.157 --> 25:26.793
The night I did that,
when I got home,

25:26.826 --> 25:28.595
there was a couple guys
in my house.

25:28.628 --> 25:29.729
Who?

25:29.762 --> 25:31.397
I don't fucking know.

25:31.430 --> 25:33.132
I took off
before they saw me.

25:33.165 --> 25:35.401
So now he's gone --
Blackstone.

25:35.434 --> 25:37.436
I mean, I don't mean
to speak ill of the dead

25:37.469 --> 25:40.740
or whatever, but it's not
the worst news I ever got.

25:40.773 --> 25:42.909
You, either, I bet.

25:42.942 --> 25:45.845
Although, you didn't
actually get the news.

25:45.878 --> 25:49.348
I mean, 'cause you were there,
on the scene.

25:49.381 --> 25:50.950
What are the odds?

25:54.887 --> 25:56.422
So, how is the wife
taking all this?

25:56.455 --> 25:58.290
She happy or what?

25:58.324 --> 26:00.126
I don't know
where she is.

26:00.159 --> 26:02.494
Oh.
Oh, that's a shame.

26:02.528 --> 26:05.832
I was thinking you would,
you two being so close --

26:05.865 --> 26:10.469
doctor-patient
and whatnot.

26:10.502 --> 26:13.039
How's this sound --
I'll check back in with you

26:13.072 --> 26:16.609
after a while
and see if you know then.

26:16.643 --> 26:20.279
Because
one of you killed him.

26:20.312 --> 26:21.513
Detective --

26:21.547 --> 26:23.616
Now you're wondering
what this is, right?

26:23.650 --> 26:27.153
But I don't know
what it is, either.

26:27.186 --> 26:29.455
I haven't decided yet.

26:29.488 --> 26:32.491
**

27:02.354 --> 27:05.357
**

27:30.649 --> 27:32.785
Look at you.

27:32.819 --> 27:38.290
[ Chuckles ]
Look at me?

27:38.324 --> 27:41.027
I thought I was never gonna
see you again.

27:41.060 --> 27:43.062
You wouldn't have.

27:43.095 --> 27:44.697
You almost didn't.

27:44.731 --> 27:46.766
What about since then?

27:46.799 --> 27:49.268
It's been weeks.
Where did you --

27:49.301 --> 27:51.704
I didn't know if you ran,
if you left town.

27:51.738 --> 27:52.939
Well, I couldn't.

27:52.972 --> 27:55.241
Not yet.

27:55.274 --> 27:57.877
How's your daughter?

27:57.910 --> 27:59.045
S-She's fine.

27:59.078 --> 28:01.247
She's safe
thanks to you.

28:01.280 --> 28:03.983
Well, she was in danger
thanks to me.

28:04.016 --> 28:05.484
Me, too.

28:05.517 --> 28:07.253
[ Keys clatter ]

28:07.286 --> 28:08.888
What about yours?

28:08.921 --> 28:11.023
Where is she now?

28:19.866 --> 28:26.072
Once you told me...
you wanted me to feel whole.

28:26.105 --> 28:30.609
That you wanted that more
than you wanted to be with me.

28:30.642 --> 28:33.579
I couldn't imagine
what you meant

28:33.612 --> 28:38.751
or who I would be
if that happened.

28:38.785 --> 28:42.121
[ Chuckles ]
And maybe it never will.

28:42.154 --> 28:44.623
Something is.

28:44.656 --> 28:47.827
Something
is happening now.

28:47.860 --> 28:51.597
[ Sighs ]
Things I thought I lost.

28:51.630 --> 28:55.768
Things I didn't know I knew,
they're coming back.

28:55.802 --> 29:00.139
And I don't want them,
but they're here.

29:00.172 --> 29:02.208
And...

29:02.241 --> 29:05.978
you deserve
to know them.

29:06.012 --> 29:09.648
You deserve to know...

29:09.681 --> 29:12.885
that you were right
about me.

29:12.919 --> 29:15.287
You were right
about my past,

29:15.321 --> 29:18.991
about my childhood,
about Jackie.

29:19.025 --> 29:20.927
You might want to sit.

29:32.071 --> 29:35.174
[ Sighs ]
Thank you, Dr. Cohen.

29:35.207 --> 29:37.209
Myra, please.

29:37.243 --> 29:42.548
I'm gonna start
with some thoughts I have.

29:42.581 --> 29:47.486
And if I'm wrong about any
of them, you stop me, all right?

29:47.519 --> 29:51.257
This refuge you've created
has kept you going,

29:51.290 --> 29:53.759
but it's also trapped you
in the past.

29:53.792 --> 29:55.928
It lets you pretend
you are a person

29:55.962 --> 29:57.930
to whom nothing has happened.

29:57.964 --> 30:01.067
But it will never let you
move forward.

30:01.100 --> 30:03.602
So, there's one thing
you must recognize --

30:03.635 --> 30:05.571
here in this office,
if nowhere else --

30:05.604 --> 30:12.111
that you will have to share with
me that you're loss is real.

30:12.144 --> 30:14.580
Can you do that, Jaclyn?

30:20.152 --> 30:22.554
Oh, before I forget,

30:22.588 --> 30:25.291
there's an earlier appointment
freeing up.
Oh, really?

30:25.324 --> 30:27.293
Yes, if you're still interested,
Mondays at 11:00.

30:27.326 --> 30:28.861
Oh, I don't know.

30:28.895 --> 30:31.363
I sort of like being
your last patient.

30:31.397 --> 30:35.201
Not worrying if someone's
left waiting while we go over.

30:35.234 --> 30:36.869
Oh, sorry.

30:36.903 --> 30:39.238
I saw my other patients
at practice today.

30:39.271 --> 30:42.141
I had forgot I had left this
in such a mess.

30:44.410 --> 30:47.079
Are you feeling
all right?

30:47.113 --> 30:49.581
I -- I just...

30:49.615 --> 30:51.750
that smell.

30:51.783 --> 30:54.620
Well, I don't...

30:54.653 --> 30:56.322
Oh, is it this,
maybe?

30:56.355 --> 30:58.891
My friend dried me some flowers
from her garden.

30:58.925 --> 31:00.960
I just --
I don't know if I can...

31:00.993 --> 31:02.828
I'll take it outside,
all right?

31:02.861 --> 31:04.663
And then
I'll open a window.

31:05.431 --> 31:07.900
Chance: It's that scent.

31:07.934 --> 31:12.338
At the same time,
she's pressing you to...

31:12.371 --> 31:14.840
share your loss.

31:14.873 --> 31:16.909
Jaclyn: Outside my window
when I was little,

31:16.943 --> 31:20.179
there was
a flowering tree.

31:20.212 --> 31:24.316
Ceanothus -- wild lilac.

31:24.350 --> 31:26.518
I didn't know
the name then.

31:26.552 --> 31:29.755
I just knew
that you could smell it

31:29.788 --> 31:33.692
even through
a locked window.

31:33.725 --> 31:36.428
Cohen: I know that
to survive this long,

31:36.462 --> 31:38.764
you've had to
keep yourself private.

31:38.797 --> 31:41.500
And by letting me in,
even as far as you have,

31:41.533 --> 31:45.004
can make you feel violated
all over again.

31:45.037 --> 31:47.273
I know that
even before you went to school,

31:47.306 --> 31:50.309
you were taught
about violence and cruelty.

31:50.342 --> 31:52.945
That the people
who were supposed to love,

31:52.979 --> 31:55.314
care for, and protect you

31:55.347 --> 31:58.050
instead violated you
beyond measure.

31:58.084 --> 32:00.953
And so, you spent
most of your life since

32:00.987 --> 32:03.322
looking for
some kind of sanctuary,

32:03.355 --> 32:05.357
trying to
make yourself to even...

32:05.391 --> 32:10.896
"...understand the idea
of safety.

32:10.929 --> 32:16.802
Telling yourself that
a small part of you still has...

32:16.835 --> 32:19.438
a living child."

32:23.775 --> 32:29.148
I wasn't very old
when I had her.

32:29.181 --> 32:32.851
And I didn't have her
for very long.

32:32.884 --> 32:35.988
I told them
she was sick.

32:36.022 --> 32:38.157
Something was wrong.

32:38.190 --> 32:41.727
They wouldn't take her
to the doctor.

32:41.760 --> 32:44.763
Jaclyn, I'm so sorry.

32:44.796 --> 32:46.032
Keep reading.

32:48.367 --> 32:51.370
And so, I know
I am trying to divest you

32:51.403 --> 32:54.840
of the most important possession
in your care now --

32:54.873 --> 32:57.109
the daughter
you couldn't save,

32:57.143 --> 33:00.779
the centerpiece
of your identity disturbance.

33:00.812 --> 33:03.715
And in doing that,
I also know I am removing

33:03.749 --> 33:05.517
your belief that you have
done something --

33:05.551 --> 33:08.120
one thing --
good with your life.

33:08.154 --> 33:10.856
But you have, Jaclyn.
You survived.

33:10.889 --> 33:12.424
You're still here.

33:12.458 --> 33:14.693
You were never allowed
to be innocent.

33:14.726 --> 33:17.029
You may always
feel alone.

33:17.063 --> 33:19.498
But it's not too late
for you to be free.

33:21.067 --> 33:22.368
Aah!

33:22.401 --> 33:24.203
[ Sobbing ]

33:24.236 --> 33:25.971
[ Gasping ]

33:32.311 --> 33:34.513
[ Gurgling ]

33:48.694 --> 33:54.266
[ Sighs, stops sobbing ]

33:54.300 --> 33:56.435
[ Gasping stops ]

34:19.225 --> 34:21.026
[ Sniffles ]

34:22.894 --> 34:28.300
[ Keys ticking ]

34:28.334 --> 34:30.469
[ Line ringing ]

34:30.502 --> 34:32.171
Blackstone: Hey.

34:32.204 --> 34:34.773
Please come.

34:34.806 --> 34:36.308
Come now.

34:38.910 --> 34:41.046
We've killed her.

34:44.015 --> 34:47.119
One night,
the winter I turned 12,

34:47.153 --> 34:50.389
I woke up and found myself
standing on the corner

34:50.422 --> 34:53.192
at the very end
of our street.

34:53.225 --> 34:55.494
I was in my pajamas...

34:55.527 --> 34:58.063
a coat, and shoes.

34:58.096 --> 35:01.300
I didn't know
how I got there.

35:01.333 --> 35:04.303
I thought
I sleepwalked.

35:04.336 --> 35:08.307
But then
I heard her...

35:08.340 --> 35:10.709
in my mind.

35:11.577 --> 35:13.345
Chance: Jackie...

35:13.379 --> 35:16.715
The real protector.

35:16.748 --> 35:20.486
That was
the very first time.

35:20.519 --> 35:29.094
And she told me, "Just
keep walking," but I didn't.

35:29.127 --> 35:31.897
I went back.

35:31.930 --> 35:34.700
Jackie the protector.

35:41.407 --> 35:43.609
Take the clothes,
put them in a bag.

35:46.578 --> 35:48.013
Jackie, you hear me?

35:48.046 --> 35:49.548
Jackie, now!

35:51.950 --> 35:53.919
Here.

36:02.894 --> 36:05.163
[ Grunting ]

36:09.435 --> 36:13.038
Protecting me
from myself.

36:13.071 --> 36:15.541
Then who --

36:15.574 --> 36:18.143
who was protecting
my daughter?

36:18.176 --> 36:20.246
Who was
protecting Nicole?

36:20.279 --> 36:23.282
Was it Jackie,
or was it you?

36:23.315 --> 36:25.784
See, maybe that's why --

36:25.817 --> 36:27.085
that's why
this has happened.

36:27.118 --> 36:30.422
That's why everything
is coming back.

36:30.456 --> 36:33.492
You have
re-entered the world.

36:33.525 --> 36:36.995
You took an action
out there in the world.

36:37.028 --> 36:40.966
Not for yourself,
but for someone else.

36:40.999 --> 36:43.569
But...

36:43.602 --> 36:44.970
This is...

36:48.974 --> 36:50.976
You told me once...

36:51.009 --> 36:53.745
to confess.

36:53.779 --> 36:58.850
To plead self-defense,
say I wasn't in my right mind.

36:58.884 --> 37:01.420
But I-I can't do that.

37:01.453 --> 37:05.090
Or I'm not strong enough
to do it.

37:05.123 --> 37:09.828
So I wrote it all down here...
for you.

37:09.861 --> 37:11.129
Jaclyn.

37:11.162 --> 37:14.199
Give it to your friend,
the good cop.

37:14.232 --> 37:17.202
I know
it's not that simple.

37:17.235 --> 37:19.438
How do you explain
how you got this

37:19.471 --> 37:23.208
or [sighs] why you haven't
shared it before now.

37:23.241 --> 37:27.112
I know I'm putting
the burden on you

37:27.145 --> 37:29.881
when you have so much more
at stake than I do,

37:29.915 --> 37:32.351
making you judge and jury.

37:32.384 --> 37:35.487
I'm sorry
if that doesn't seem fair.

37:56.207 --> 38:01.547
D: You see a move, don't wait.
Go first. Trust your training.

38:01.580 --> 38:03.749
Be the still point
in the turning world.

38:03.782 --> 38:05.351
Wait! Fuck!

38:05.384 --> 38:07.786
You hold the blade in place
for a two-count...

38:14.526 --> 38:15.894
No!

38:15.927 --> 38:17.563
You're not the one.

38:20.699 --> 38:21.967
Aah!

38:24.570 --> 38:27.539
What?
What is it?

38:33.412 --> 38:36.682
We all have blood
on our hands.

38:36.715 --> 38:39.585
It's not the same.

38:39.618 --> 38:44.222
We are all pilgrims...

38:44.255 --> 38:46.358
trying to figure out
who we are

38:46.392 --> 38:48.794
and how to live
in this world.

38:48.827 --> 38:51.329
And we go on
until we can't.

39:17.355 --> 39:20.459
[ Door opens, shuts ]

39:42.681 --> 39:47.018
S'up, buddy?

39:47.052 --> 39:50.288
Chance: First, the S.F. cop
took my clothes,

39:50.321 --> 39:52.858
asked way too many
questions.

39:52.891 --> 39:56.194
Then Detective Hynes says
that he's not sure

39:56.227 --> 39:59.498
if he's
blackmailing me yet.

39:59.531 --> 40:02.834
And I am left
with her confession,

40:02.868 --> 40:06.037
this powder keg
in my keeping.

40:06.071 --> 40:08.474
Beyond my connection
with her,

40:08.507 --> 40:10.341
am I worried that the detective
who knows about it

